<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Sidecar entitlements for the bundled PyInstaller `magi` runtime.

  These are applied when the release pipeline deep-signs every Mach-O under
  binaries/magi/ (the `magi` executable and every .so/.dylib in _internal/)
  BEFORE `cargo tauri build` bundles the tree into Contents/Resources/magi/.
  See .github/workflows/desktop-release-macos.yml and README.md.

  A frozen CPython interpreter (PyInstaller onedir) CANNOT run under the macOS
  Hardened Runtime without these three exceptions; without them the child
  crashes on launch instead of serving. Each is required and scoped only to the
  sidecar process, never to the outer shell:

    com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit
      CPython and several native deps allocate executable memory pages (JIT /
      trampolines). Hardened Runtime blocks this by default.

    com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory
      PyInstaller's bootloader maps and executes the interpreter and extension
      code from memory that is not backed by a signed on-disk page. Required or
      the process is killed with a codesign / hardened-runtime violation.

    com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation
      The onedir _internal/ tree contains many .dylib/.so files that are signed
      with OUR Developer ID but are not all Apple-notarized-as-a-team libraries;
      it also dlopen()s plugins at runtime. Library validation would refuse to
      load dylibs whose Team ID differs, so it must be disabled for this process.

  Security trade-off (documented, accepted): these three relax memory-integrity
  and library-provenance guarantees FOR THE SIDECAR PROCESS ONLY. This is the
  standard, unavoidable entitlement set for shipping a notarized frozen-Python
  binary under Hardened Runtime. The shell (entitlements.plist) keeps the full
  Hardened Runtime with no exceptions, and the runtime binds loopback only.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
  <dict>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
    <true/>
  </dict>
</plist>
